<p>Temperature-dependent lattice parameters of a, b and c for orthorhombic Ti
 <sub>3</sub>Sn obtained from XRD profiles were shown in 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="materials-12-02484-f007">Figure 7</xref>. It could be seen that parameter a reduced during cooling, parameter c remains almost constant, and parameter b increased during cooling. The d-spacing of (hkl) plane in orthorhombic phase is calculated according to Equation (2):
 <disp-formula id="FD1-materials-12-02484">
  <label>(2)</label>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>hkl</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mrow>
       <msqrt>
        <mrow>
         <msup>
          <mrow>
           <mfenced>
            <mrow>
             <mfrac>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>
             </mfrac>
            </mrow>
           </mfenced>
          </mrow>
          <mn>2</mn>
         </msup>
         <mo> </mo>
         <mo>+</mo>
         <mo> </mo>
         <msup>
          <mrow>
           <mfenced>
            <mrow>
             <mfrac>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">k</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">b</mi>
             </mfrac>
            </mrow>
           </mfenced>
          </mrow>
          <mn>2</mn>
         </msup>
         <mo> </mo>
         <mo>+</mo>
         <mo> </mo>
         <msup>
          <mrow>
           <mfenced>
            <mrow>
             <mfrac>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">c</mi>
             </mfrac>
            </mrow>
           </mfenced>
          </mrow>
          <mn>2</mn>
         </msup>
        </mrow>
       </msqrt>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
